      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fort_Edward%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The village of Fort Edward was officially created in 1849, spurred by the arrival of the Glens Falls railroad in 1869.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15,
        17
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://villageoffortedward.gov/history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Old Fort House Museum, standing on the original fort site, joined the National Register of Historic Places in 1983.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fort_Edward%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "James Episcopal Church began serving the community in 1844, followed shortly by the Village Baptist Church in 1848.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
